## Matching

`name` is matched against the OpenStack project names in your Cleura account — the same
names shown in the Cleura Cloud control panel and listed by the `cleura` CLI. The match is:

- **Exact** — the whole name must match; no substrings, globs, or prefixes.
- **Case-sensitive** — `My-Project` and `my-project` are treated as different projects.
- **Region-scoped** — only projects in the provider's `region` are considered. `region` is
  a case-sensitive region tag (for example `Sto2`, `Fra1`, `Kna1`) taken from the provider
  configuration or the `CLEURA_*` environment — never from the `cleura` CLI. A project name
  that exists only in another region will not be found here.

If no project in the region matches the name, the plan fails with a "Project not found"
error.

-> **Note:** This is a data source, so it is **read-only**: it looks its value up on every
plan and apply and creates nothing. There is no resource to manage and nothing to
`terraform import`.

